 "Cells" -> {<|"Data" -> ".md\n# Fireflies or Nature's Cellular \
Automaton\nThis blog post was originally inspired by a beautiful piece \
written by physicist [Cian Luke Martin: \"Fireflies, Magnets and \
Emergence\"](https://www.cianlm.dev/blog/Fireflies_Magnets_and_Emergence). He \
demonstrates a very clear way of modeling the collective behavior of \
fireflies at night\[LongDash]as a sort of cellular automaton. I couldn't help \
but think: I should try this out!\n\n> Have you ever wondered how each \
firefly knows when to blink? How do they coordinate across the fields and \
trees?\n\n\n\nWell, I guess we're heading towards a __many-body \
problem__...\n\nFollowing Cian's basic model, each firefly needs:\n- an \
internal state or clock\n- a flash (and a sensor)\n\nThe last component \
indicates the end of the internal clock cycle and broadcasts to all other \
fireflies so they can synchronize their clocks as well. Therefore, we can \
represent each firefly as a flow chart:", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "978051a2-0fba-4cdd-ab87-c16db67366da", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "78c489a0-70db-4ca8-9f9a-ec192481c803"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "# Fireflies or Nature's Cellular Automaton\nThis blog post \
was originally inspired by a beautiful piece written by physicist [Cian Luke \
Martin: \"Fireflies, Magnets and \
Emergence\"](https://www.cianlm.dev/blog/Fireflies_Magnets_and_Emergence). He \
demonstrates a very clear way of modeling the collective behavior of \
fireflies at night\[LongDash]as a sort of cellular automaton. I couldn't help \
but think: I should try this out!\n\n> Have you ever wondered how each \
firefly knows when to blink? How do they coordinate across the fields and \
trees?\n\n\n\nWell, I guess we're heading towards a __many-body \
problem__...\n\nFollowing Cian's basic model, each firefly needs:\n- an \
internal state or clock\n- a flash (and a sensor)\n\nThe last component \
indicates the end of the internal clock cycle and broadcasts to all other \
fireflies so they can synchronize their clocks as well. Therefore, we can \
represent each firefly as a flow chart:", "Display" -> "markdown", 
    "Hash" -> "91dab865-b6b1-486f-9e8a-5813d2f506bc", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "78c489a0-70db-4ca8-9f9a-ec192481c803"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".mermaid\nflowchart LR\n    decayAction[Decay]\n    \
decayCheck{Decayed?}\n    flash[Flash]\n    adjust[Adjust]\n\n    decayAction \
--> decayCheck\n    decayCheck -- Yes --> flash\n    decayCheck -- No --> \
adjust\n    adjust --> decayAction\n    flash --> adjust", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "a70b6f8b-a26b-42b3-8a7d-30d04357f389", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "78c489a0-70db-4ca8-9f9a-ec192481c803"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "flowchart LR\n    decayAction[Decay]\n    \
decayCheck{Decayed?}\n    flash[Flash]\n    adjust[Adjust]\n\n    decayAction \
--> decayCheck\n    decayCheck -- Yes --> flash\n    decayCheck -- No --> \
adjust\n    adjust --> decayAction\n    flash --> adjust", 
    "Display" -> "mermaid", "Hash" -> "6787a169-41b9-40ef-a6be-728bc91e8e13", 
    "Invisible" -> False, "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "78c489a0-70db-4ca8-9f9a-ec192481c803"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".md\n__TLDR;__\nIf you really want to see the final result:", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "ca6bb0c4-27ba-4aee-8a7a-79efe2e816f9", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "78c489a0-70db-4ca8-9f9a-ec192481c803"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "__TLDR;__\nIf you really want to see the final result:", 
    "Display" -> "markdown", "Hash" -> 
     "8a30f121-c21e-41b3-aa59-8159900bb89d", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "78c489a0-70db-4ca8-9f9a-ec192481c803"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "Module[{f = RandomReal[{0,1.01}, {25,25}]}, Refresh[\n  \n  f \
= Map[Clip[# - 0.01, {0.0,1.0}, {1.0,1.0}]&, f, {2}];\n\n  f = Clip[f + (2.0 \
Round[f] - 1.0) \
Clip[ListConvolve[{{1.0,1.0,1.0},{1.0,0.0,1.0},{1.0,1.0,1.0}}, Floor[f], 2, \
0], {0,  0.001}], {0., 1.0}];  \n  \n  ArrayPlot[f, Frame->True, \
ColorFunction->\"PlumColors\"]\n, 1/30.0]]", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "cbfea720-8f54-4586-8732-fa66bd44fb30", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Fade" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "78c489a0-70db-4ca8-9f9a-ec192481c803"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".md\nThe question is: __how does it adjust itself?__\nThere \
are multiple models for this case. We'll pick the simplest approach, assuming \
that:\n1. the cycle duration of each firefly is the same and fixed;\n2. when \
a flash emitted by another firefly is seen, the internal phase or clock is \
adjusted forward or backward slightly, depending on which is closer.\n\nIn \
this model, our fireflies are out of phase initially and are trying to align \
with each other. Since the visibility of another firefly's flash signal \
depends on distance, we can naturally limit the number of \"visible\" \
neighbors\[LongDash]limiting the interaction distance.\n\nLet's define a \
function that will distribute `n` points over a given region:", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "fb550c62-eb6f-4708-b601-8307ab5442a9", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "78c489a0-70db-4ca8-9f9a-ec192481c803"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "The question is: __how does it adjust itself?__\nThere are \
multiple models for this case. We'll pick the simplest approach, assuming \
that:\n1. the cycle duration of each firefly is the same and fixed;\n2. when \
a flash emitted by another firefly is seen, the internal phase or clock is \
adjusted forward or backward slightly, depending on which is closer.\n\nIn \
this model, our fireflies are out of phase initially and are trying to align \
with each other. Since the visibility of another firefly's flash signal \
depends on distance, we can naturally limit the number of \"visible\" \
neighbors\[LongDash]limiting the interaction distance.\n\nLet's define a \
function that will distribute `n` points over a given region:", 
    "Display" -> "markdown", "Hash" -> 
     "364f70a3-918c-41d2-a734-15adc30259be", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "78c489a0-70db-4ca8-9f9a-ec192481c803"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "generateFireFlies[n_:200, region_:Rectangle[{-10,-10}, \
{10,10}]] := fireFlies = With[{\n  pos = RandomPoint[region, n]\n},\n  \
Transpose[{pos, Table[ RandomReal[{0,1.0}], {Length[pos]}]}]\n];", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "6448ce0e-3ed9-47b3-9502-4560f56cf498", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"InitGroup" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "78c489a0-70db-4ca8-9f9a-ec192481c803"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".md\nHere, a firefly is represented as a list of two objects: \
\n - `position`;\n - `state` - a real-valued number (randomly generated):", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "aaef326c-e434-4cc3-b056-b38ec8e9c14d", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "78c489a0-70db-4ca8-9f9a-ec192481c803"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "Here, a firefly is represented as a list of two objects: \n - \
`position`;\n - `state` - a real-valued number (randomly generated):", 
    "Display" -> "markdown", "Hash" -> 
     "9f4d7285-4e29-46d9-9577-3e074b235ffa", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "78c489a0-70db-4ca8-9f9a-ec192481c803"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "generateFireFlies[1] // First ", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "d583da58-12e5-4e11-8967-1d62c535bf7e", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "78c489a0-70db-4ca8-9f9a-ec192481c803"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> 
     "{{-5.896003641067651`,1.7548145516864455`},0.1972596724287563`}", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "5c3a6140-facc-4311-a177-d32057c14ac7", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "78c489a0-70db-4ca8-9f9a-ec192481c803"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".md\nFor the next step, we find all nearest fireflies and \
bake all the connections within a given radius into a `connectionMatrix`:", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "42e1b818-7408-45aa-ad0d-b1cf25c1dc8a", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "78c489a0-70db-4ca8-9f9a-ec192481c803"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "For the next step, we find all nearest fireflies and bake all \
the connections within a given radius into a `connectionMatrix`:", 
    "Display" -> "markdown", "Hash" -> 
     "7e30b9ce-9f95-4d4f-8856-e667d4ef1daa", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "78c489a0-70db-4ca8-9f9a-ec192481c803"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "bakeConnections[r_:3.7] := (\n  connectionMatrix = Table[\n  \
If[i==j, Infinity, (*SpB[*)Power[Norm[i[[1]] - \
j[[1]]](*|*),(*|*)2](*]SpB*)]\n, {i, fireFlies}, {j, fireFlies}];\n  \
connectionMatrix = MapIndexed[Function[{value, index}, \n  If[value < r, \
index[[1]], Nothing]\n], #] &/@ connectionMatrix\n);", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "aedf23ea-71ea-46f2-9dee-28973224c590", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"InitGroup" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "78c489a0-70db-4ca8-9f9a-ec192481c803"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".md\nFor example, if we generate 10 fireflies and highlight \
all neighbors:", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "24310b69-9a5a-4539-91d6-0aee9e24f107", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "78c489a0-70db-4ca8-9f9a-ec192481c803"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> 
     "For example, if we generate 10 fireflies and highlight all neighbors:", 
    "Display" -> "markdown", "Hash" -> 
     "5b5bdafe-d2a4-47a6-9412-dcee9c100482", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "78c489a0-70db-4ca8-9f9a-ec192481c803"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "generateFireFlies[10, \
Disk[{0,0},10]];\nbakeConnections[30.0];\nGraphics[{\n  Blue, Table[\n    \
Line[{fireFlies[[i,1]], fireFlies[[#,1]]}]&/@connectionMatrix[[i]], \n    \
{i,Length[fireFlies]}\n  ],\n  Red, Disk@@#&/@fireFlies\n}, ImageSize->250]", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "8b3deffa-c5d7-4ad0-9789-212ff60ed4bc", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "78c489a0-70db-4ca8-9f9a-ec192481c803"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "(*VB[*)(FrontEndRef[\"41d66f5c-464c-42d3-90cd-a22ed5e23d6e\"]\
)(*,*)(*\"1:eJxTTMoPSmNkYGAoZgESHvk5KRCeEJBwK8rPK3HNS3GtSE0uLUlMykkNVgEKmximm\
JmlmSbrmpiZAAmjFGNdS4PkFN1EI6PUFNNUI+MUs1QAgegV0A==\"*)(*]VB*)", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "e376b53a-5f27-4397-a8ee-3dc24a4825a4", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "78c489a0-70db-4ca8-9f9a-ec192481c803"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".md\nDo you remember our flow chart? Flashing and decaying \
are rather simple: we count down our state from 1.0 to 0.0, and once 0 is \
reached, we reset it back to 1.0\[LongDash]our flash signal. Here we define \
all 3 functions we need:", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "93a15154-1c17-4489-bfc9-32179ec1424b", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "78c489a0-70db-4ca8-9f9a-ec192481c803"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "Do you remember our flow chart? Flashing and decaying are \
rather simple: we count down our state from 1.0 to 0.0, and once 0 is \
reached, we reset it back to 1.0\[LongDash]our flash signal. Here we define \
all 3 functions we need:", "Display" -> "markdown", 
    "Hash" -> "0fa5a11a-58fd-4b6f-8c9f-1a72de28bc93", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "78c489a0-70db-4ca8-9f9a-ec192481c803"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "decay[{pos_, state_}] := {pos, Clip[state - 0.01, \
{0,1}]};\nflash[{pos_, state_}] := {pos, If[state == 0, 1, \
state]};\nadjust[{pos_, 0}, index_] := {pos, 0}\nadjust[{pos_, state_}, \
index_] := With[{i = index[[1]]},\n {pos, \
If[Or@@Thread[fireFlies[[connectionMatrix[[i]], 2]] == 1],\n   Clip[state + \
Sign[2 Round[state] - 1] 0.0001, {0,1}],\n   state\n ]}\n]", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "eba968be-44ca-4a36-a5ef-6049440cc970", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"InitGroup" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "78c489a0-70db-4ca8-9f9a-ec192481c803"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".md\n`adjust` is the most interesting one, since we also need \
to scan over all visible neighbors and then, if one is in the \"flashing\" \
state (1.0), we push our internal clock forward or backward depending on \
which is closer to the flashing state of 1.0.", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "f25eed5d-28d6-4b50-ba36-3d66fd1e2b36", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "78c489a0-70db-4ca8-9f9a-ec192481c803"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "`adjust` is the most interesting one, since we also need to \
scan over all visible neighbors and then, if one is in the \"flashing\" state \
(1.0), we push our internal clock forward or backward depending on which is \
closer to the flashing state of 1.0.", "Display" -> "markdown", 
    "Hash" -> "dfad3935-06d5-4fa8-967e-fd7f16d45a4d", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "78c489a0-70db-4ca8-9f9a-ec192481c803"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> ".md\nNow we create a global cycle:", 
    "Display" -> "codemirror", "Hash" -> 
     "e87b3fee-f4cb-44f7-8831-b1ca8ccc3c79", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <|"Hidden" -> True|>, 
    "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Input", 
    "UID" -> Null, "Notebook" -> "78c489a0-70db-4ca8-9f9a-ec192481c803"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "Now we create a global cycle:", "Display" -> "markdown", 
    "Hash" -> "9c898016-3d07-43c0-9af9-c78e7bbe65c1", "Invisible" -> False, 
    "MetaOnly" -> False, "Props" -> <||>, "PublicFields" -> {"Properties"}, 
    "State" -> "Idle", "Type" -> "Output", "UID" -> Null, 
    "Notebook" -> "78c489a0-70db-4ca8-9f9a-ec192481c803"|>, 
   <|"Data" -> "update = Function[Null,\n  fireFlies = decay /@ fireFlies;\n  \
fireFlies = flash /@ fireFlies;\n  fireFlies = MapIndexed[adjust, \
fireFlies];\n];", "Display" -> "codemirror", 
    "Hash" -> "5954fc33-e426-46db-a8a2-f6e1ea6dcefd", "Invisible" -> False, 
